g.text: Search Robots by Designation or Task
Deployment of one of the RFP modules in a DEI VM to be systematic, validating on a scheduled basis with the test plan
Only customers on the DEI internal network (wired or via VPN) to be able to access the solution
The clients indicated in the previous user story to be able to be defined by simply changing a text file
Identify and quantify the risks involved in the recommended solution
MBCO (Minimum Business Continuity Objective) to be proposed to stakeholders to be defined
Backup strategy to be proposed, justified and implemented that minimizes the RPO (Recovery Point Objective) and the WRT (Work Recovery Time)
Define a public folder for all users registered in the system
Obtain users with more than 3 incorrect accesses
Disaster recovery plan that satisfies the MBCO defined in sprint B
Changes to be made to the infrastructure to be presented in a justified manner in order to ensure an MTD (Maximum Tolerable Downtime) of 20 minutes

Backup copy of the DB(s) to be made to a Cloud environment using a script that renames it to the format <db_name>_yyyymmdd with <db_name> being the name of the database, yyyy the year the copy was made, mm the month the copy was made and dd the day the copy was made

Use the Backup created in US 840 to create a script that manages the files resulting from this backup, within the following schedule. 1 Backup per month for the last year, 1 backup per week for the last month, 1 backup per day for the last week
DB backup US process to be kept in the Linux log, in an appropriate context, and the administrator is alerted when accessing the console if a serious failure occurs in this process
Backup copy of the US of the DB backup to have a lifespan of no more than 7 (seven) days, except as indicated in the US of retention of monthly and annual copies
A BIA (Business Impact Analysis) of the final solution to be presented to me, adapting if and where applicable the risk(s) identified in the previous sprint
Access management to be implemented that meets the appropriate security criteria
Clustering system to be implemented in a justified manner between the systems that implement the SPA
Have SSH access to the virtual machine, only through a certificate, without using a password
A public file share to be created between the various teams, in SMB/CIFS or NFS format

Must ensure that, if necessary, backups were carried out correctly. To do this, we must automate its replacement, ultimately validating the functioning of the system (Ex. Database - execute a successful SQL query after replacement)
